theorem Topology.interior_compl_eq_compl_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    interior (Aᶜ) = (closure A)ᶜ := by
  -- Start from the companion lemma applied to the complement of `A`.
  have h : closure A = (interior (Aᶜ))ᶜ := by
    simpa [Set.compl_compl] using
      (Topology.closure_compl_eq_compl_interior (X := X) (A := Aᶜ))
  -- Taking complements of both sides yields the desired equality.
  have h' : (closure A)ᶜ = interior (Aᶜ) := by
    simpa using congrArg Set.compl h
  simpa using h'.symm

theorem Set.compl_compl {α : Type*} (s : Set α) : sᶜᶜ = (s : Set α) := by
  ext x
  simp
